mention.text: the last lynching of a black man in the American West
Marshall , hanged amid a bitter later strike
the Rev. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. , Davis and other religious leaders
a ceremony of `` reconciliation and forgiveness
the phrase that stuck in my mind all these years : ' a necktie party
The same racism that shot Martin Luther King in Memphis
the same prejudice that strung up Marshall in Price
the all-white mob that lynched an itinerant black miner suspected of murdering a coal company guard
a long editorial denouncing the reconciliation day as an imported hodgepodge of `` correct political thinking , rewriting of history and victim culture

President Clinton 's call for a national dialogue on race that inspired him and the other organizers to plan ceremonies at the resting place of a lynching victim who for 73 years has lain in an unmarked grave
a result of the controversy brought on by plans for the gathering
